item.title: NUMBERS and LETTERS - BUILDING IDENTIFICATION SIGNS - 100mm SERIES
item.description:
3D print - NUMBERS and LETTERS - BUILDING IDENTIFICATION SIGNS - 100mm SERIES

In order to test the parts from the BUILDING IDENTIFICATION SIGNS - 100mm SERIES, you are now able to download for free the "7L, 7C AND 7R" letters, to print and see if you are happy with the final result.

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/home/numbers-and-letters-building-identification-signs

Not a physical product ! STL format.

All parts are check for naked edges or errors.

In order to print with two colors, without using a dual filaments 3d printer, when the base job is complete, and the printer is starting to print the number (after the 1st or second layer), pause the printer and switch the filament. Restart the job. You will end with a part in two colors!

If you have any difficulties in printing this part, please let me know! We will try to fix it together!

Design to print without support ... :) By Costa

3D PRINTING SETTINGS
Design was made for a print using 0.4mm nozzle, 0.8mm in/out walls, 20 infill.

In order to print with two colors, without using a dual filaments 3d printer, when the base job is complete, and the printer is starting to print the number (after the 1st or second layer), pause the printer and switch the filament. Restart the job. You will end with a part in two colors!

item.title: Sink and Disposal Strainer
item.description:
Yet Another Sink Strainer: Keep your measuring spoons and teaspoons from going down the disposal! And keep the bulk of the food from going down -- using the disposal for anything but small scraps is notorious for clogging drain and sewer lines.

My friends wanted one or two each. I measured their sinks and found three common sizes. STL files are provided for those (3 in = 76.2 mm, 3 1/8 in = 79.4 mm, 3 1/4 in = 83.0 mm).

In addition, the OpenSCAD source file is included to allow customization. For that, open it in OpenSCAD, use the Customizer Window to modify parameters as desired using F5 to preview, and when satisfied press F6 to render followed by F7 to save as STL.

By default, the handle is decoratively faceted. It can be removed, or rounded into a sphere by increasing $fn. The curb around the outside can be raised, lowered or removed. The number of rows and columns of holes and the size of the holes are under your control.

If printed in PLA and you pour hot pasta water over it, it may sag slightly toward the middle, but it's not too bad. PLA is not harmed by water (I have a running experiment with some pieces in water and they remain unchanged after 6 months).

item.title: Banana Lamp 1.0
item.description:
This is a banana lamp I designed for fun. It could be a lovely night lamp for yourself or a surprise gift for your friends.

I modified the structure several times, and printed 5 prototypes, in order to make the light inside looks perfect, even tried the downwards LED Bulb setup. Only a small area needs support, the 4 peels legs and the center of the body. I use 0.2mm level height and 40% infill to save time, almost 19 hours in my machine to print the body.

The Bulb is LED bulb（less than 3.5W) with E12/E14 base. You can buy kinds of stuff on Amazon. See the last image for the assembly instructions.

You can also download or buy my other mushroom lamps :

item.title: 150g Fork Wedge Battlebot
item.description:
Wedge Robot This is a 150g combat robot. I'm attaching the .STEP file as well for those who want to edit.

Please note as shown this robot does not hit 150g. The robot sits at about 175g as configured. The suggested wheels are 45g for the four. Easiest way to make weight is to use lighter 28mm wheels.

Notes:

Forks can be printed or laser cut from 6mm Titanium. Upload the DXF to SendCutSend.com

The N20s are a snug fit in the chassis. But I use a ziptie just to make sure they are secure.

Use M3 Heatset inserts on the front of the body to attach the wedge mount.

Use #3 Plastite screws for the top panels.

BOM:

Solarbotics RW2 Wheel 28mm https://www.pololu.com/product/642

Small 4" Zip Ties

3-24 Plastite Screws

M3 Heat Set Inserts: McMaster 94180A331

M3 x 6 Button Heads: McMaster 92095A179

M3 x 25 Button Head: McMaster 97763A457

M3 Nut: McMaster 90592A085

Electronics:

ESC: Malenki Nano
US: (https://turnabot.com/shop/parts/malenki_nano_rtu/)
UK: https://shop.bristolbotbuilders.com/product/malenki/

Drive Motors:

N10s are better if your trying to make weight. N20s are easier to source but usually less powerful.
High Power N10s: https://turnabot.com/shop/parts/high-power-n10/

TX: FLYSKY FS-i6X:

Battery: 300mah 2S Lipo Pack: (https://turnabot.com/shop/parts/turnigy-2s-300mah-lipo/)
